<div class="ingredients">
    <h3><strong>Ingredients</strong></h3>
    <ul>
        <li>2/3 cup butter (141g)</li>
        <li>1 1/3 cup sugar (265g)</li>
        <li>3 large eggs</li>
        <li>3 1/4 cups all-purpose flour (406g)</li>
        <li>1 tablespoon baking powder</li>
        <li>2/3 cup - 1 cup mix-ins per loaf (recipe makes 2 loaves, optional. We did 1/3 cup of each: almond, dried cranberries, and white chocolate. As well as 1/2 cup each: chocolate chips, chopped pecan pieces for the other loaf.)</li>
        <li>3 tablespoons cocoa powder, 1 tablespoon oil (if making a loaf of chocolate biscotti)</li>
    </ul>
    <h3><strong>Directions</strong></h3>
    <ol>
        <li>Preheat oven to 350F and prepare a cookie sheet with parchment paper.</li>
        <li>Using a mixer, beat together the sugar and butter. You want to incorporate a lot of air into the mixture now - do not be afraid to overbeat it.</li>
        <li>Add the eggs, one at a time, mixing well between each addition.</li>
        <li>Mix in the vanilla extract.</li>
        <li>In a separate bowl, mix the flour, baking powder, and salt together.</li>
        <li>Slowly add the dry ingredients into the wed, mixing until well combined.</li>
        <li>Divide the cookie dough in half and place in separate bowls. Add the desired mix-ins to each bowl.</li>
        <li>Form each ball of dough into a log shape with squared off sides. It should measure about 10" long, 3" wide, and 1" tall. Make sure there is some room around each loaf to allow for expansion. The dough may be a little sticky to work with here, so you can flour your hands if that is the case. Press any additional toppings on top, if desired.</li>
        <li>Bake for 30 minutes, until golden brown and firm.</li>
        <li>Remove from the oven and leave until it is cooled completely (this is important).</li>
        <li>Slice the loaves into roughly 1"-2" inch thick slices, and place back onto the baking sheet (you may need to use a second one).</li>
        <li>Place bake into the 350F oven and cook for another 20 minutes, flipping the biscotti halfway through.</li>
        <li>Leave the biscotti to cool and finish firming up, then enjoy! The biscotti will last for a few weeks at room temperature in an airtight container.</li>
    </ol>
</div>
</div>





